sortedCountMap

public java.util.SortedMap<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Integer> sortedCountMap()
this method returns a TreeMap that has : - keys are the counts of the items which has same "counts" in the Counting set. For example if Set includes {abc:4, cde:3, efg:4, jkl:1, mno:1, xyz:1} then the TreeMap will have this values {1:3, 3:1, 4:2} saying that there are 3 items with count of 1, 1 item with count 3, and 2 items with count of 4.

Returns:
a TreeMap containing count of items and their total counts.
